# Bottom Navigation Bar (App Style)

## 1. Layout & Positioning
- **Position:** `fixed` or `absolute` at the `bottom: 0` of the `#phone-frame`.
- **Constraint:** Must ALWAYS remain visible above scrolling content (`z-index: 100`).
- **Safe Area:** Incorporate `padding-bottom: var(--safe-bottom)` to prevent the Home Indicator from overlapping icons.
- **Dimensions:** Height of `56px` + `var(--safe-bottom)`.

## 2. Component Specifications
- **Structure:** Use a `<nav>` tag containing an unordered list (`<ul>`) with exactly 4-5 items.
- **Items:** - Each item must be a `flex` column (Icon on top, Label on bottom).
    - Label font size: `10px` or `12px`.
    - Active State: Use an `.active` class to change icon/label color (e.g., brand primary).
- **Interactions:**
    - Use `justify-content: space-around` for equal spacing.
    - Provide haptic-like feedback (subtle scale transform on tap).

## 3. CSS Blueprint
```css
.bottom-nav {
  position: absolute;
  bottom: 0;
  left: 0;
  right: 0;
  height: calc(56px + var(--safe-bottom));
  background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.95);
  backdrop-filter: blur(10px); /* iOS style blur */
  border-top: 1px solid #eee;
  display: flex;
  justify-content: space-around;
  align-items: flex-start; /* Align to top of nav to leave safe-bottom empty */
  padding-top: 8px;
  padding-bottom: var(--safe-bottom);
  z-index: 100;
}

.nav-item {
  flex: 1;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  align-items: center;
  text-decoration: none;
  color: #8E8E93; /* iOS Gray */
}

.nav-item.active {
  color: #007AFF; /* iOS Blue / Brand Primary */
}

.nav-item i {
  font-size: 24px;
  margin-bottom: 4px;
}